 President Muhammadu Buhari, on Monday, extended the COVID-19 lockdown on Ogun, Lagos and Abuja by another 14 days. The President disclosed this decision in a nationwide broadcast on latest developments on the Covid-19 pandemic. He said, “With this in mind, and having carefully considered the briefings and report from the President Task Force and the various options offered, it has become necessary to extend the current restriction in Lagos and Ogun states, as well as the FCT, for another 14 days, effective from 11.59pm on Monday 13th April 2020. I am, therefore, once again asking you all to work with Government in this fight.” Details later… 